Cheese Dumpings with Smoked Chilli Jam

250g manioc starch (tapioca)
200g finely grated aged cheddar
3 eggs
24g softened unsalted butter
2-3 tbsp milk

Preheat oven to 400F. Tip the manioc starch and cheese into a large bowl and rub together with your fingertips until the mixture resembles breadcrubs. Gradually incorporate the eggs, butter, and milk until you have a smooth, soft dough. Roll the mixture into small balls and place into mini muffin trays (~3x12)
Bake for 12-15m until pale gold in color. Allow to cool slightly before serving.

2 ancho chillies, soakd in hot water for 30 min
3 cloves smoked garlic, peeled and crushed
250g caster sugar (superfine not powdered) 
200mm white wine vinegar
1 tsp chilli flakes
1 tsp smoked paprika


Drain the soaked ancho chillies, remove the stems and finely chop. Put into a saucepan with the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 5 min until thickened. Remove from the heat and leave to cool before serving.
